REVELLERS gathered for spontaneous rendition after Scotland game on Sunday night - check out the video here. Scots clubbers stage an impromptu singalong of Proclaimers' 500 miles in Glasgow's Sauchiehall Street - Daily Record SCOTS clubbers couldn’t resist an impromptu singalong of 500 Miles after the Scotland Game on Sunday night.
In the wee hours of Monday morning a mass of revellers gathered in Glasgow’s Sauchiehall Street to do their own version of The Proclaimers smash hit.

The crowd gathered shortly before 3am on the street to surround a lad with a guitar , jump and fist pump the air as they chorused on the well known song.&nbsp;A witness said: “Where else in the world do you get this walking down the street?”
Another commented: “Pure dead brilliant.”
 